    "links.filter_links()\n",
    "oracle.get_cluster_specific_TFdict_from_Links(links_object=links)\n",
    "oracle.fit_GRN_for_simulation(alpha=10, use_cluster_specific_TFdict=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 3. in silico Perturbation-simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "Next, we will simulate  the effects of perturbing a single TF to investigate its function and regulatory mechanism.\n",
    "See the celloracle paper for the details and scientific premise on the algorithm.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we'll show an example of the simulation; we'll simulate knock-out of  Gata1 gene in the hematopoiesis. \n",
    "\n",
    "Previous studies have shown that Gata1 is one of the TFs that regulates cell fate decisions in myeloid progenitors. Additionally, Gata1 has been shown to affect erythroid cell differentiation. \n",
    "\n",
    "Here, we will analyze Gata1 for the demonstration of celloracle; Celloracle try to recapitulate the previous findings of Gata1 gene above."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.1. Check gene expression pattern."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 989.28x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 265,
       "width": 935
      },
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Check gene expression \n",
    "goi = \"Gata1\"\n",
    "sc.pl.draw_graph(oracle.adata, color=[goi, oracle.cluster_column_name],\n",
    "                 layer=\"imputed_count\", use_raw=False, cmap=\"viridis\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

      ]

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Plot gene expression in histogram\n",
    "sc.get.obs_df(oracle.adata, keys=[goi], layer=\"imputed_count\").hist()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.2. calculate future gene expression after perturbation.\n",
    "\n",
    "Although you can use any gene expression value for the input of in silico perturbation, we recommend avoiding extreme values which are far from natural gene expression ranges. If you set Gata1 gene expression to 100, for example, it may lead to biologically infeasible results.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we simulate Gata1 KO; we predict what happens to the cells if Gata1 gene expression changed into 0."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Enter perturbation conditions to simulate signal propagation after the perturbation.\n",
    "oracle.simulate_shift(perturb_condition={goi: 0.0},\n",
    "                      n_propagation=3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.3. calculate transition probability between cells\n",
    "\n",
    "In the step above, we simulated simulated future gene expression values after perturbation. This prediction is based on itelative calculations of signal propagations within the GRN.\n",
    "\n",
    "Next step, we will calculate the probabilityof a cell state transition based on the simulated data. Using the transition probability between cells, we can predict how a cell changes after perturbation.\n",
    "\n",
    "This transition probability will be used in two ways.\n",
    "\n",
    "(1) Visualization of directed trjectory graph.\n",
    "\n",
    "(2) Markof simulation.\n",
    "\n",
    "In Step 4.2 and 4.3, we usefunctions imported from the velocytoloom class in velocyto.py. Please see the documentation of VelocytoLoom for more information. http://velocyto.org/velocyto.py/fullapi/api_analysis.html"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/home/k/anaconda3/envs/test/lib/python3.6/site-packages/IPython/core/interactiveshell.py:3326: FutureWarning: arrays to stack must be passed as a \"sequence\" type such as list or tuple. Support for non-sequence iterables such as generators is deprecated as of NumPy 1.16 and will raise an error in the future.\n",
      "  exec(code_obj, self.user_global_ns, self.user_ns)\n",
      "WARNING:root:Nans encountered in corrcoef and corrected to 1s. If not identical cells were present it is probably a small isolated cluster converging after imputation.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Get transition probability\n",
    "oracle.estimate_transition_prob(n_neighbors=200, knn_random=True, sampled_fraction=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate embedding \n",
    "oracle.calculate_embedding_shift(sigma_corr = 0.05)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate global trend of cell transition\n",
    "oracle.calculate_grid_arrows(smooth=0.8, steps=(40, 40), n_neighbors=300)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 4. Visualization\n",
    "## 4.1. Detailed directed trajectory graph"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(None,(6,6))\n",
    "quiver_scale = 40\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "ix_choice = np.random.choice(oracle.adata.shape[0], size=int(oracle.adata.shape[0]/1.), replace=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "embedding = oracle.adata.obsm[oracle.embedding_name]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(embedding[ix_choice, 0], embedding[ix_choice, 1],\n",
    "            c=\"0.8\", alpha=0.2, s=38, edgecolor=(0,0,0,1), lw=0.3, rasterized=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "quiver_kwargs=dict(headaxislength=7, headlength=11, headwidth=8,\n",
    "                   linewidths=0.35, width=0.0045,edgecolors=\"k\",\n",
    "                   color=oracle.colorandum[ix_choice], alpha=1)\n",
    "plt.quiver(embedding[ix_choice, 0], embedding[ix_choice, 1],\n",
    "           oracle.delta_embedding[ix_choice, 0], oracle.delta_embedding[ix_choice, 1],\n",
    "           scale=quiver_scale, **quiver_kwargs)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.axis(\"off\")\n",
    "#plt.savefig(f\"{save_folder}/full_arrows{goi}.png\",  transparent=True)"
   ]

    "Based on the results, we may conclude several things as follows.\n",
    "\n",
    "Gata1 KO induced both cell state transitions from Erythroids to MEP, and from MEP to GMP.\n",
    "\n",
    "(1) These results suggest that Gata1 may play a role in the progression of Erythroid differentiation and cell state determination between the MEP and GMP lineages.\n",
    "\n",
    "(2) Gata1 KO also induced cell state transitions from granulocytes to late GMP, suggesting Gata1's involvement in Granulocytes differentiation.\n",
    "\n",
    "These results agree with previous reports about Gata1 and recapitulate Gata1's cell-type-specific function regarding the cell fate decisions in hematopoiesis."
